.DT
add_immune_to
Disk World creator help
add_immune_to

.SH Name
.SP 5 5
add_immune_to -  This adds a new type of damage that the object is immune to.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SI 5
void add_immune_to(mixed args)
.EI

.SH Parameters
.SI 5
%^BOLD%^args%^RESET%^ - the type of damage to be immune to
.EI

.SH Defined in
.SI 5
/std/basic/wearable.c
.EI

.SH Description
.SP 5 5

This adds a new type of damage that the object is immune to.
The parameter can either be a string or an array of strings
being the types of damage to be immune to.
.EP

.SH Example 1
.SI 5
inherit "/std/basic/wearable";

void setup() {
   ...
   add_immune_to("sharp");
   ...
} /* setup() */
.EI

.SH Example 2
.SI 5
inherit "/std/basic/wearable";

void setup() {
   ...
   add_immune_to("sharp");
   ...
} /* setup() */
.EI

.SH See also
.SP 5 5
remove_immune_to(), query_immune_to()

.EP

